      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BOAB BOY (3) finished off strongly to just miss at this track and trip last time out, ending up 1.3L off the winner as a $10 chance. This looks to set up similarly for him and the firmer footing on offer looks a big tick. Has his hoof on the till and can land the knockout blow this time. THE SHOWVINIST (5) closed off steadily when getting well back last start, finishing behind BOAB BOY on that occasion. A better draw this time may see him a touch closer in the run and the firmer footing looks as though it increases his chances. Can play a leading role. SATURDAY SESH (4) missed by 1.3L at this track and trip two back before holding his own in town lasts tart with a midfield finish. Back to the scene of the crime now and he rates highly on his recent efforts. Not out of this. TWIST OF GOLD (9) got back to form last start and won't be far away if she can run up to that level again. PRAWNS ELEVEN (1) will find this a more suitable race and can't be left out.",
